summary: The tamping rod is a round, straight steel rod used with concrete cylinder molds, slump cones, and unit weight tests. Measures 5/8" diameter by 24" length. Both ends are rounded to a hemispherical tip. The tamping rod is plated for rust resistance and has a 6" scale in 1/4" increments engraved on end of the rod for measuring the slump.
For handling concrete, sand, and soils in the laboratory and or field.
